extends wcopyright

block head
  title Maowtm Image Server

block content
  img.servericon(src=mapStatic('/svg/imgIndexIcon.svg'))
  h1 img.maowtm.org
  p This is a little server used for storing static and uploaded image. It can deal with scaling and formatting.
  .main
    h2 Usage
    p All image can be accessed with this URL:
    pre #{'https://img.maowtm.org/<name>'}
    p As an example, we will use the famous Lenna image:
    -const imgMaowtm = 'https://img.maowtm.org/'
    -let lenna = mapStatic('/imgs/lenna.png')
    -let imgName = lenna.replace(imgMaowtm, '')
    pre
      = imgMaowtm
      span.imgName= imgName
    p
      |( Notice that the name here is 
      code.imgName= imgName
      |  )
    img(src=lenna)
    hr
    p
      | Sometime you may want a smaller image, maybe display as a little icon. You specity the desired 
      b minimum
      |  width with the 
      code width
      |  query argument. For example, the following URL give you a 50x50 image:
    pre= lenna + '?width=50'
    img(src=lenna+'?width=50')
    p The width will get ceiled to the nearest 50, which means
    pre= lenna + '?width=20'
    img(src=lenna+'?width=20')
    p gives you the same result.
    hr
    p You can also convert the format. The following URL gives you an JPG image of 100x100
    pre= lenna + '?width=100&as=jpg'
    img(src=lenna+'?width=100&as=jpg')
    p Notice that without the <code>as</code> thing, all image is given in PNG.
    hr
    p If you get your name wrong and get a 404, you will still get an image.
    img(src=imgMaowtm + 'somethingnotexist')
    p Notice that query string still apply, even if 404.
    pre= imgMaowtm + 'somethingnotexist' + '?width=200'
    img(src=imgMaowtm + 'somethingnotexist' + '?width=200')

